    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-08-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-08-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="294"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d294">
                <head>294. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Central Intelligence Agency</gloss>
                    Station in Saigon to the <gloss type="to">Agency</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d294fn1">Source: National Defense University,
                            <persName corresp="#p_TGMD1">Taylor</persName> Papers, T-172-69. Top
                        Secret. The source text is a copy sent by the <gloss target="#t_CIA1"
                            >CIA</gloss> to the Joint Chiefs of Staff exclusive for <persName
                            corresp="#p_KMGVH1">Krulak</persName> who was to pass it exclusive to
                            <persName corresp="#p_LMGEG1">Lansdale</persName>. Copies were also sent
                        to the White House for <persName corresp="#p_FMV1">Forrestal</persName> and
                        the Department of State for <persName corresp="#p_HTL1">Hughes</persName>
                        and <persName corresp="#p_HR1">Hilsman</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <placeName>Saigon</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1963-08-26">August 26, 1963</date>
                        </hi>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[<hi rend="italic">document number and 1 sentence containing document number not
                        declassified</hi>]</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Following message received from <gloss target="#t_CAS1">CAS</gloss>
                        officer who now at Pleiku: <list>
                            <label>a.</label>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_KHANH1">Khanh</persName> was not ready move
                                now. Plan was to wait until <persName corresp="#p_NHU1"
                                    >Nhu</persName> moved in direction rapprochement with <gloss
                                    target="#t_DRV1">DRV</gloss> then strike. This would give
                                Generals some legal grounds for move.</item>
                            <label>b.</label>
                            <item>Still hopes <persName corresp="#p_NHU1">Nhu</persName> will
                                provide pretext on which Generals can hang action. Quoting <gloss
                                    target="#t_VOA1">VOA</gloss> broadcast said hope was we would
                                cut aid and if <persName corresp="#p_DIEM1">Diem</persName> yields
                                and fires <persName corresp="#p_NHU1">Nhu</persName> then no need
                                revolt. My impression he much prefers it that way. Wanted know if
                                “secret police to be punished Der <gloss target="#t_VOA1"
                                    >VOA</gloss> includes <persName corresp="#p_NHU1"
                                >Nhu</persName>.” I replied <persName corresp="#p_NHU1"
                                    >Nhu</persName> must go. He nodded.</item>
                            <label>c.</label>
                            <item>Talking to <persName corresp="#p_KHIEM1">Khiem</persName> without
                                his approval was wrong move but no damage. <persName
                                    corresp="#p_KHANH1">Khanh</persName> going Saigon for hour or so
                                tonight.</item>
                            <label>d.</label>
                            <item>We must not talk to <persName corresp="#p_DINH1">Dinh</persName>.
                                Also <gloss target="#t_CAS1">CAS</gloss> officer be careful of tight
                                surveillance.</item>
                            <label>e.</label>
                            <item>Wants immediate reply to single request: will we guarantee safe
                                haven and support to families in case Generals fail? Have no money
                                stashed away.</item>
                            <label>f.</label>
                            <item>Impression: <persName corresp="#p_KHANH1">Khanh</persName> caught
                                off base by our timing does not quite know what to do.</item>
                            <label>g.</label>
                            <item>Recommend phone <persName corresp="#p_KHIEM1">Khiem</persName>
                                number 30102 that I returning Saigon tonight, if you so instruct. We
                                awaiting your instructions.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_CAS1">CAS</gloss> officer being instructed return tomorrow
                        after an additional meeting with <persName corresp="#p_KHANH1"
                            >Khanh</persName> or without, whichever seems useful. We not replying
                        pare 1e pending discussion with Ambassador.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
